l progress.","keyPoints":["Ignition usmjerava nacionalnu svemirsku politiku u operativne korake","Fisijska površinska energija ključna za trajnu mjesečevu bazu","Međunarodna svemirska postaja dobiva novu ulogu u planu"],"source":{"name":"","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BYH6W9iCs2E"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/nasas-ignition-plan-science-first-spectacle-second/main.jpg","alt":"NASA-in plan 'Ignition': Nauka i baza za Mjesec u fokusu"},"subtitle":"Tri programa, jedan cilj: od orbite do trajnih istraživačkih postaja","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/nasas-ignition-plan-science-first-spectacle-second/subtitle.png","alt":"Tri programa, jedan cilj: od orbite do trajnih istraživačkih postaja"},"tags":["NASA","Lunar Base","Space Exploration"],"geo":{"name":"Washington, D.C., USA","lat":38.9072,"lon":-77.0369,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$7","videoUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BYH6W9iCs2E","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-23-starships-sixth-flight-proves-reuse-is-the-real-ra","dbId":639,"title":"Starshipov šesti let: korak bliže ponovnoj uporabi cijelog sustava","category":"space","date":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Starshipov šesti let: korak bliže ponovnoj uporabi cijelog sustava","execSummary":"SpaceX's sixth Starship test marks a shift from spectacle to operational validation, with the Super Heavy booster demonstrating critical reuse maneuvers. The real significance lies in economic implications: full system reuse could drop orbital launch costs by an order of magnitude, enabling Mars missions and commercial orbital infrastructure. Next steps focus on orbital refueling simulations in Q1 2025, moving from testing to operational reality.","keyPoints":["33 Raptor motora uspješno podigli Super Heavy s lansa","Prvi potvrđeni povratni manevar booster-a nakon odvajanja","Ključni test za ekonomiju svemirskih letova"],"source":{"name":"","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CMGiNKcVSek"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/starships-sixth-flight-proves-reuse-is-the-real-ra/main.jpg","alt":"Starshipov šesti let: korak bliže ponovnoj uporabi cijelog sustava"},"subtitle":"Ponovna uporaba nije samo cilj – to je uvjet za Mars i komercijalnu orbitu","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/starships-sixth-flight-proves-reuse-is-the-real-ra/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Ponovna uporaba nije samo cilj – to je uvjet za Mars i komercijalnu orbitu"},"tags":["Starship","Reusability","Mars Mission","SpaceX"],"geo":{"name":"Starbase, Boca Chica, Texas, USA","lat":25.9972,"lon":-97.1561,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$8","videoUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CMGiNKcVSek","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-23-complete-genetic-alphabet-found-in-asteroid-ryugu-","title":"Asteroid Ryugu otkrio sve genetičke 'slova' života – što to znači?","category":"space","date":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kada je japanska sonda Hayabusa2 2020.","execSummary":"The discovery of all five nucleobases in Ryugu’s samples shifts the debate from *whether* life’s building blocks exist in space to *how common* they are—and what that implies for abiogenesis. This article dissects the mission’s precision, the scientific weight of a complete nucleobase set, and why this demands a rethink of prebiotic chemistry’s universality.","keyPoints":["Sva pet nukleobaza pronađeno u uzorcima asteroida Ryugu","Otkriće sugerira širinu građevnih blokova života u svemiru","JAXA-i Hayabusa2 misija ključna za analizu uzoraka"],"source":{"name":"Phys.org Space","url":"https://phys.org/news/2026-03-fundamental-life-genetic-code-asteroid.html"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/complete-genetic-alphabet-found-in-asteroid-ryugu-/main.jpg","alt":"Asteroid Ryugu otkrio sve genetičke 'slova' života – što to znači?"},"subtitle":"Zašto je ovo više od samo kemije – a kamo sreće u potrazi za podrijetlom života","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/complete-genetic-alphabet-found-in-asteroid-ryugu-/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto je ovo više od samo kemije – a kamo sreće u potrazi za podrijetlom života"},"tags":["Asteroid Ryugu","Origin of Life","Astrobiology"],"geo":{"name":"Sagamihara, Kanagawa, Japan [JAXA Institute of Space and Astronautical Science (ISAS) - Hayabusa2 mission control]","lat":35.5976,"lon":139.3889,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$9","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-23-extragalactic-archaeology-maps-spiral-galaxy-evolu","title":"Galaktička arkeologija otkriva dinamiku spiralne galaktike","category":"space","date":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kada astronomi govore o 'arheologiji svemira', obično misle na rekonstrukciju prošlosti naše galaktike kroz analizu zvijezda i plina.","execSummary":"This study shifts galactic archaeology from the Milky Way to external galaxies, using chemical fingerprints to reconstruct their evolution—proving direct historical analysis is possible beyond simulations. The real impact lies in validating (or challenging) galaxy formation theories with empirical timelines, not just visual data.","keyPoints":["Prva rekonstrukcija povijesti galaktike izvan Mliječnog puta","Kemijski otisci prstiju kao ključ za evoluciju svemira","Novo polje: vanjska galaktička arkeologija otvara vrata"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/extragalactic-archaeology-maps-spiral-galaxy-evolu/main.jpg","alt":"Galaktička arkeologija otkriva dinamiku spiralne galaktike"},"subtitle":"Metoda koja mijenja način na koji razumijemo rast udaljenih galaktika","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/extragalactic-archaeology-maps-spiral-galaxy-evolu/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Metoda koja mijenja način na koji razumijemo rast udaljenih galaktika"},"tags":["Galactic Archaeology","Spiral Galaxy Dynamics","Galaxy Evolution"],"geo":{"name":"San Francisco, US","lat":37.7749,"lon":-122.4194,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$a","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-23-how-eu-law-is-quietly-reshaping-gaming-hardware-de","title":"Switch 2 i EU pravo: zašto je zamjenjiva baterija korak naprijed","category":"space","date":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kada europski zakonodavci 2021.","execSummary":"Nintendo’s Switch 2 redesign for EU markets—mandating user-replaceable batteries—isn’t just a gaming story but a test case for how regulation can enforce sustainability in closed-tech ecosystems. The move, driven by EU consumer law, challenges industry norms and could set a precedent for modular design in electronics, with broader implications for e-waste reduction and right-to-repair advocacy.","keyPoints":["EU propis prisiljava dizajnersku promjenu Switch 2","Zamjenjiva baterija kao standard za potrošačke uređaje","Što ovo znači za trajnost i reciklaciju igračih konzola"],"source":{"name":"Eurogamer","url":"https://www.eurogamer.net/thanks-to-eu-consumer-law-nintendo-is-updating-the-switch-2-design-to-enable-european-players-to-replace-the-battery"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/how-eu-law-is-quietly-reshaping-gaming-hardware-de/main.jpg","alt":"Switch 2 i EU pravo: zašto je zamjenjiva baterija korak naprijed"},"subtitle":"Kako regulativa oblikuje hardver — i zašto je to važno izvan igara","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/how-eu-law-is-quietly-reshaping-gaming-hardware-de/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Kako regulativa oblikuje hardver — i zašto je to važno izvan igara"},"tags":["European Union","Sustainable Electronics","Right to Repair"],"geo":{"name":"Kyoto, Japan","lat":35.0116,"lon":135.7681,"countryCode":"JP"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$b","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-23-obesity-therapy-could-determine-mars-mission-viabi","title":"Kombinirana terapija za gojaznost: manji masnoće, očuvani mišići","category":"space","date":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kada se govori o gojaznosti u kontekstu dugoročnih svemirskih misija, problem prestaje biti estetski ili čak isključivo medicinski — pretvara se u operativni rizik.","execSummary":"A phase 2 trial combining semaglutide and bimagrumab shows unprecedented fat loss with muscle preservation, offering potential solutions for long-duration space missions where muscle atrophy is a critical risk. The findings bridge metabolic research and space medicine, but raise questions about long-term safety and ethical use beyond clinical needs.","source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/obesity-therapy-could-determine-mars-mission-viabi/main.jpg","alt":"Kombinirana terapija za gojaznost: manji masnoće, očuvani mišići"},"subtitle":"Novi pristup liječenju metaboličkih bolesti u svemiru i na Zemlji","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/obesity-therapy-could-determine-mars-mission-viabi/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Novi pristup liječenju metaboličkih bolesti u svemiru i na Zemlji"},"tags":["space"],"geo":{"name":"Baton Rouge, Louisiana, United States","lat":30.4515,"lon":-91.1871,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$c","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-23-orbitiny-a-linux-desktop-that-bends-the-rules-of-p","title":"Orbitiny: Linux stolna okolina koja radi kao aplikacija u svemiru računarstva","category":"space","date":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"U svijetu gdje svaki gram mase i svaka milisekunda odziva mogu odlučiti između uspjeha i propasti misije, Orbitiny se pojavljuje kao tihi revolucionar.","execSummary":"Orbitiny, a Linux desktop that runs like an app, offers portability and performance without installation. This could revolutionize space research computing by simplifying system deployment in resource-limited environments like spacecraft or research stations.","keyPoints":["Linux desktop bez instalacije","Portabilnost za znanstvena računala","Snaga i jednostavnost kao ključna prednost"],"source":{"name":"ZDNet","url":"https://www.zdnet.com/article/orbitiny-portable-modular-unique-linux-desktop/"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/orbitiny-a-linux-desktop-that-bends-the-rules-of-p/main.jpg","alt":"Orbitiny: Linux stolna okolina koja radi kao aplikacija u svemiru računarstva"},"subtitle":"Zašto je ovo važno za budućnost istraživanja svemirskih operativnih sustava?","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/orbitiny-a-linux-desktop-that-bends-the-rules-of-p/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto je ovo važno za budućnost istraživanja svemirskih operativnih sustava?"},"tags":["Orbitiny","Linux","Space Operating Systems"],"geo":{"name":"Houston, TX","lat":29.5502,"lon":-95.097,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$d","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-22-astronomers-sound-alarm-over-orbiting-mirror-propo","title":"Zvijezde pod optužbom: Kako megakonstelacije prijete astronomiji","category":"space","date":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Noćno nebo, kako ga čovječanstvo poznaje otkad je prvi put podiglo pogled prema zvijezdama, možda se suočava s nepovratnom promjenom.","execSummary":"This article examines the scientific and operational consequences of two megaconstellation projects—orbital mirrors and SpaceX's million AI satellites—through the lens of astronomical research. It dissects why these initiatives threaten decades of observational progress and exposes the regulatory vacuum enabling their unchecked expansion.","keyPoints":["Astronomi protestiraju protiv orbitalnih ogledala i AI satelita","Milijun novih satelita može trajno izmijeniti noćno nebo","Znanstvena zajednica traži regulaciju svemirskih megaprojekata"],"source":{"name":"Space.com","url":"https://www.space.com/space-exploration/satellites/this-is-really-intolerable-astronomers-protest-giant-orbiting-mirror-project-and-spacexs-million-ai-satellites"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/astronomers-sound-alarm-over-orbiting-mirror-propo/main.jpg","alt":"Zvijezde pod optužbom: Kako megakonstelacije prijete astronomiji"},"subtitle":"Projekti koji obećavaju tehnološki napredak mogu uništila milijunima godina neizmijenjen pogled u svemir","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/astronomers-sound-alarm-over-orbiting-mirror-propo/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Projekti koji obećavaju tehnološki napredak mogu uništila milijunima godina neizmijenjen pogled u svemir"},"tags":["Satellite Constellations","Orbital Debris","Space Pollution"],"geo":{"name":"Hawthorne, United States","lat":33.9192,"lon":-118.3384,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$e","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-22-mars-gravity-poses-new-questions-for-astronaut-mus","title":"Marsova gravitacija: Tihe prijetnje astronautskom zdravlju","category":"space","date":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Marsova gravitacija privlači pogled znanstvenika i svemirskih agencija već desetljećima, ali jedna od najtiših prijetnji njegovog okoliša ostaje slabo istražena: utjecaj njegove gravitacije, koja iznosi samo 38% zemljine, na ljudsko tijelo.","execSummary":"An international research team led by Marie Mortreux is studying how Mars's lower gravity could severely impact astronauts' skeletal muscles, posing a major challenge for long-term missions. This analysis explores the scientific significance, potential solutions, and what it means for the future of human space exploration beyond Earth orbit.","keyPoints":["Marsova gravitacija 38% Zemljine","Mišična atrofija kao glavni rizik","URI tim istražuje dugoročne posljedice"],"source":{"name":"Universe Today","url":"https://www.universetoday.com/articles/how-will-martian-gravity-affect-skeletal-muscle"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/mars-gravity-poses-new-questions-for-astronaut-mus/main.jpg","alt":"Marsova gravitacija: Tihe prijetnje astronautskom zdravlju"},"subtitle":"Utjecaj Marsove gravitacije na ljudsko tijelo: zašto je ovo istraživanje ključno za buduće misije?","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/mars-gravity-poses-new-questions-for-astronaut-mus/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Utjecaj Marsove gravitacije na ljudsko tijelo: zašto je ovo istraživanje ključno za buduće misije?"},"tags":["Mars Mission","Astronaut Health","Space Exploration"],"geo":{"name":"Rhode Island, USA","lat":41.7423,"lon":-71.7601,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$f","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-22-mit-s-injectable-livers-could-transform-transplant","title":"Mini jetre za injekciju: transplantacija bez skalpela?","category":"space","date":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kada je riječ o transplantaciji organa, najveći izazovi nisu samo tehnički, već i logistički: nedostatak donora, rizici velikih kirurških zahvata i dugoročna odbijanja.","execSummary":"MIT’s injectable 'satellite livers' challenge the transplant status quo by offering a minimally invasive alternative to organ replacement. This article examines the scientific significance—reducing donor dependency and surgical risks—while framing the unresolved questions (scalability, long-term viability) that will determine whether this becomes a clinical reality or remains a promising experiment.","keyPoints":["MIT-ovi inženjeri razvili funkcionalne „satelitske jetre“","Gel-zaštićene stanice otvaraju put minimalno invazivnim zahvatima","Ključni korak prema rješavanju nedostatka organa za presadbu"],"source":{"name":"NotebookCheck","url":"https://www.notebookcheck.net/Injectable-mini-livers-show-promise-as-transplant-alternative-after-successful-test.1256348.0.html"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/mit-s-injectable-livers-could-transform-transplant/main.jpg","alt":"Mini jetre za injekciju: transplantacija bez skalpela?"},"subtitle":"Zašto bi ovo moglo promijeniti budućnost transplantologije — i koje su sljedeće prepreke","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/mit-s-injectable-livers-could-transform-transplant/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto bi ovo moglo promijeniti budućnost transplantologije — i koje su sljedeće prepreke"},"tags":["Organ Transplantation","Transplantology","Medical Innovation"],"geo":{"name":"Cambridge, Massachusetts, United States","lat":42.3601,"lon":-71.0942,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$10","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-20-biodegradable-robot-finger-turns-to-soil","title":"Biorazgradivi robotski prst: rješenje za svemirski otpad?","category":"space","date":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kada se govorilo o zagađenju svemira, mislilo se uglavnom na orbitalni otpad — ostaci satelita i raketa koji kruže Zemljom.","execSummary":"The first fully biodegradable robotic actuator isn’t just an eco-gimmick—it’s a direct response to the unaddressed problem of space debris *on* other planets. Cornell’s gelatine-cellulose composite could redefine mission sustainability by eliminating permanent waste, but scalability and extreme-environment durability remain untested. The real question: should this become the default for all future off-world hardware?","keyPoints":["Prvi potpuno kompostabilni mehanički aktulator","Elektronski otpad u svemiru — hitan problem bez rješenja","Potencijal za održive misije na Mars i dalje"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/biodegradable-robot-finger-turns-to-soil/main.jpg","alt":"Biorazgradivi robotski prst: rješenje za svemirski otpad?"},"subtitle":"Zašto bi svaki budući rover trebao moći nestati u tlu?","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/biodegradable-robot-finger-turns-to-soil/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto bi svaki budući rover trebao moći nestati u tlu?"},"tags":["Space Debris","Biodegradable Robotics","Planetary Rover"],"geo":{"name":"Ithaca, United States","lat":42.4534,"lon":-76.4735,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$11","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-20-blue-origin-s-51-600-satellite-plan-for-orbital-ai","title":"Blue Origin šalje AI u orbitu: 51.600 satelita mijenja igru","category":"space","date":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Blue Origin, tvrtka Jeffa Bezosa, podnijela je zahtjev Federalnoj komisiji za komunikacije (FCC) za lansiranje 51.","execSummary":"Blue Origin plans to launch 51,600 satellites for an orbital AI data center, potentially shifting computing power to space. This initiative could redefine space infrastructure, but raises questions about coordination, capacity, and long-term impact on space exploration and technology.","keyPoints":["51.600 satelita za orbitalna AI centra","Sun-sinkrone orbite od 311 do 1.118 milja","Projekt nadopunjuje zemaljske podatkovne centre"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/blue-origin-s-51-600-satellite-plan-for-orbital-ai/main.jpg","alt":"Blue Origin šalje AI u orbitu: 51.600 satelita mijenja igru"},"subtitle":"Zašto Project Sunrise nije samo još jedna konstelacija","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/blue-origin-s-51-600-satellite-plan-for-orbital-ai/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto Project Sunrise nije samo još jedna konstelacija"},"tags":["Blue Origin","Project Sunrise","Satellite Constellation"],"geo":{"name":"Kent, Washington, United States","lat":47.380933,"lon":-122.234889,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$12","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-20-canada-s-200m-spaceport-bet-a-sovereignty-play","title":"Kanada gradi prvi svemirski luk: 200 milijuna za Nova Škotsku","category":"space","date":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kada je kanadski ministar nacionalne obrane, david mcguinty, 16.","execSummary":"Canada’s $200M investment in Nova Scotia’s first commercial spaceport isn’t just about launch infrastructure—it’s a strategic move toward orbital autonomy. By reducing reliance on foreign launch sites, Canada gains control over satellite deployment timelines, critical for Arctic monitoring and scientific missions. The real test will be whether Maritime Launch Services can deliver on cost competitiveness and operational reliability by the 2025 target.","keyPoints":["Prvi kanadski komercijalni svemirski luk u Nova Škotskoj","200 milijuna dolara za infrastrukturu pod kontrolom Maritime Launch Services","Korak prema samostalnom pristupu svemiru za Kanadu"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/canada-s-200m-spaceport-bet-a-sovereignty-play/main.jpg","alt":"Kanada gradi prvi svemirski luk: 200 milijuna za Nova Škotsku"},"subtitle":"Zašto ovo nije samo o lansiranju raketa, već o strategijskoj autonomiji","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/canada-s-200m-spaceport-bet-a-sovereignty-play/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto ovo nije samo o lansiranju raketa, već o strategijskoj autonomiji"},"tags":["Canada","Spaceport","Nova Scotia"],"geo":{"name":"Canso, Nova Scotia, Canada","lat":45.35,"lon":-61.0167,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$13","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-20-cotton-candy-worlds-defy-jwst-behind-impenetrable-","title":"Cuker-pamuk egzoplaneti: granica Webbovih mogućnosti","category":"space","date":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kada čak i James Webb Space Telescope — najmoćniji svemirski teleskop ikad izgrađen — naleti na neprobojnu prepreku, znanstvena zajednica mora preispitati ne samo instrumente, nego i sama očekivanja.","execSummary":"The discovery that Webb cannot penetrate the haze around ultra-low-density 'cotton candy' exoplanets forces a reckoning with observational limits—not just for this telescope, but for exoplanet science as a whole. The article examines why this matters beyond spectacle: it exposes a blind spot in atmospheric study methods and demands rethinking of future mission designs.","keyPoints":["Najmanje gušći egzoplaneti ikad otkriveni","Magla blokira Webbove instrumente bez obzira na valnu duljinu","Atmosferska analiza zaustavljena – što slijedi u istraživanju?"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/cotton-candy-worlds-defy-jwst-behind-impenetrable-/main.jpg","alt":"Cuker-pamuk egzoplaneti: granica Webbovih mogućnosti"},"subtitle":"Zašto je ovo više od samo 'zanimljive anomalije' — i kako mijenja planove za buduća promatranja","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/cotton-candy-worlds-defy-jwst-behind-impenetrable-/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto je ovo više od samo 'zanimljive anomalije' — i kako mijenja planove za buduća promatranja"},"tags":["Exoplanets","Webb Space Telescope","Space Observation"],"geo":{"name":"Global","lat":0,"lon":0,"countryCode":"XX"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$14","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-20-ohios-7-ton-meteorite-a-rare-delivery-from-the-sol","title":"Lov na meteorit u Ohiju: Zašto je ovo važno za znanost?","category":"space","date":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kad je 7-tonski svemirski kamen [ušao u Zemljinu atmosferu](https://phys.","execSummary":"The 7-ton Ohio meteorite isn’t just a visual spectacle—it’s a direct sample of the early solar system’s building blocks. This article cuts through the spectacle to explain why its fragments matter for planetary science, how recovery efforts are coordinated, and what unanswered questions linger about asteroid composition and Earth’s origins.","keyPoints":["7-tonski svemirski kamen eksplodirao nad Ohijom","Fragmenti mogu otkriti sastav rane Sunčeve sustave","NASA-ini podaci potvrđuju putanju i masu"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/ohios-7-ton-meteorite-a-rare-delivery-from-the-sol/main.jpg","alt":"Lov na meteorit u Ohiju: Zašto je ovo važno za znanost?"},"subtitle":"Od spektakla do znanosti: Kako se iz meteora izvlači vrijedna informacija","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/ohios-7-ton-meteorite-a-rare-delivery-from-the-sol/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Od spektakla do znanosti: Kako se iz meteora izvlači vrijedna informacija"},"tags":["Meteorite","Ohio","Planetary Science"],"geo":{"name":"San Francisco, US","lat":37.7749,"lon":-122.4194,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$15","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-19-spin-speed-finally-separates-giant-planets-from-br","title":"Brže vrtnje odvajaju planete od smeđih patuljaka","category":"space","date":"2026-03-19T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-19T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Desetljećima su astronomi bili pred dilemom: kako razlikovati divovske planete od smeđih patuljaka, objekata masivnijih od planeta, ali premalenih da započnu nuklearnu fuziju poput zvijezda.","execSummary":"Northwestern University's discovery that spin speed distinguishes giant planets from brown dwarfs resolves a decades-old classification challenge. This operational metric simplifies identification without complex spectroscopy, with implications for formation theories and future telescope missions like JWST.","keyPoints":["Spin razlikuje divovske planete i smeđe patuljke","Preklapajuća svojstva zbunjivala znanstvenike desetljećima","Sjeverozapadno sveučilište otkriva presudnu razliku"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/spin-speed-finally-separates-giant-planets-from-br/main.jpg","alt":"Brže vrtnje odvajaju planete od smeđih patuljaka"},"subtitle":"Razumijevanje svemirskih tijela na granici planeta i zvijezda","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/spin-speed-finally-separates-giant-planets-from-br/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Razumijevanje svemirskih tijela na granici planeta i zvijezda"},"tags":["Exoplanets","Brown Dwarfs","Planetary Formation"],"geo":{"name":"Evanston, United States","lat":42.0451,"lon":-87.6877,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$16","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-17-how-photonic-ski-jumps-could-rewrite-spacecraft-de","title":"Mikroskopske „skakaonice“ mogu LiDAR svesti na veličinu čipa","category":"space","date":"2026-03-17T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-17T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Svaki gram u orbiti je bitka.","execSummary":"The article examines how MIT's 'photonic ski-jump' LiDAR technology could eliminate mechanical mirrors in spacecraft systems, drastically reducing SWaP constraints. It contextualizes this within NASA/ESA's push for solid-state solutions and explores operational implications for lunar/Mars missions, while clearly distinguishing confirmed lab results from speculative field performance.","keyPoints":["Fotonijske „skakaonice“ zamjenjuju klompe mehaničke ogledala u LiDAR-u","SWaP parametri (veličina, težina, potrošnja) ključni za buduće svemirske misije","MIT, MITRE i Sandia National Labs objavili rad u *Nature* s potencijalom za serijsku primjenu"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/how-photonic-ski-jumps-could-rewrite-spacecraft-de/main.jpg","alt":"Mikroskopske „skakaonice“ mogu LiDAR svesti na veličinu čipa"},"subtitle":"Zašto bi ova tehnologija mogla promijeniti način kako svemirska letjelica ‘gleda’ i komunicira","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/how-photonic-ski-jumps-could-rewrite-spacecraft-de/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto bi ova tehnologija mogla promijeniti način kako svemirska letjelica ‘gleda’ i komunicira"},"tags":["LiDAR","Spacecraft Navigation","Microscopy"],"geo":{"name":"Cambridge, MA, USA","lat":42.3601,"lon":-71.0942,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$17","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-17-jwst-discovers-new-exoplanet-class-with-distinctiv","title":"Novi tip egzoplaneta: otkriće koje mijenja razumijevanje atmosferâ","category":"space","date":"2026-03-17T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-17T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kada James Webb Space Telescope (JWST) usmjeri svoje zrcalo prema nepoznatom, znanstvena zajednica ne očekuje spektakl — već podatke koji će promijeniti modele.","execSummary":"The discovery of sulfur dioxide in HD 189733 b’s atmosphere via JWST isn’t about sensationalism—it’s a critical data point challenging planetary formation models. This article frames why sulfur chemistry matters for exoplanet science and what operational shifts it demands from upcoming missions like Ariel.","keyPoints":["James Webb otkrio planet s sumporovodikom u atmosferi","Potvrđena nova klasa egzoplaneta — ali miris nije prioritet","Što ovo znači za potragu za nastanjivim svjetovima?"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/jwst-discovers-new-exoplanet-class-with-distinctiv/main.jpg","alt":"Novi tip egzoplaneta: otkriće koje mijenja razumijevanje atmosferâ"},"subtitle":"Zašto je otkriće neobičnog sastava važnije od senzacionalizma o 'smradu'","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/jwst-discovers-new-exoplanet-class-with-distinctiv/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto je otkriće neobičnog sastava važnije od senzacionalizma o 'smradu'"},"tags":["Exoplanet","Atmospheric Composition","Space Discovery"],"geo":{"name":"Menlo Park, CA","lat":37.4529,"lon":-122.1817,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$18","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-17-moon-bases-need-room-to-growliterally-heres-the-be","title":"Širenje mjesečevih baza: NASA-ini planovi i milijuni u igri","category":"space","date":"2026-03-17T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-17T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Kada je riječ o trajnom ljudskom prisutstvu na Mjesecu, svaki kubni metar prostora postaje strateški resurs.","execSummary":"Voyager Technologies' multi-million dollar investment in Max Space signals a strategic push to solve NASA’s Artemis program’s critical bottleneck: how to transport and deploy enough habitable volume for sustained lunar presence. The article analyzes why expandable habitats—offering up to 3x more space post-deployment—could redefine mission logistics, while noting unresolved challenges like regolith abrasion and NASA’s parallel evaluations of competing designs.","keyPoints":["Voyager ulaže milijune u Max Space za širenje mjesečevih modula","Expandabilni habitati ključni za Artemisove dugotrajne misije","NASA još nije službeno potvrdila uporabu — ali signal je jasan"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/moon-bases-need-room-to-growliterally-heres-the-be/main.jpg","alt":"Širenje mjesečevih baza: NASA-ini planovi i milijuni u igri"},"subtitle":"Zašto bi upravo ova tehnologija mogla odrediti budućnost ljudskog boravka na Mjesecu","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/moon-bases-need-room-to-growliterally-heres-the-be/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto bi upravo ova tehnologija mogla odrediti budućnost ljudskog boravka na Mjesecu"},"tags":["NASA","Lunar Base","Space Exploration"],"geo":{"name":"Menlo Park, CA","lat":37.4529,"lon":-122.1817,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$19","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-17-moons-patchy-magnetism-finally-explained-after-60-","title":"Magnetna zagadka Mjeseca: 60 godina čekanja na odgovor","category":"space","date":"2026-03-17T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-17T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Šezdeset godina znanstvenici znaju da Mjesec nema globalno magnetsko polje koje bi ga štitilo od solarnog vjetra, ali i da na njegovoj površini postoje lokalne ’oaze’ s magnetnim poljem do deset puta jačim od okoline.","execSummary":"This article explains why the Moon's localized magnetic anomalies—up to 10x stronger than background levels—matter beyond scientific curiosity: they reveal Earth-Moon interactions from 4 billion years ago and have direct implications for Artemis mission safety. The focus is on operational significance, not spectacle.","keyPoints":["Mjesečeve magnetne anomalije do 10 puta jače od pozadine","Solarni vjetar i opasni nabijeni regolit bez zaštitnog omotača","Nove spoznaje o interakciji Mjeseca i Zemljine magnetosfere"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/moons-patchy-magnetism-finally-explained-after-60-/main.jpg","alt":"Magnetna zagadka Mjeseca: 60 godina čekanja na odgovor"},"subtitle":"Zašto su lokalne magnetne ’oaze’ ključne za buduće misije — i što nam još nedostaje","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/moons-patchy-magnetism-finally-explained-after-60-/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto su lokalne magnetne ’oaze’ ključne za buduće misije — i što nam još nedostaje"},"tags":["Moon Exploration","Lunar Magnetism","Space Mission Planning"],"geo":{"name":"San Francisco, US","lat":37.7749,"lon":-122.4194,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$1a","lang":"hr"},{"id":"2026-03-17-rfx-fuse-revives-breimans-lost-vision-for-machine-","title":"RFX-Fuse: Šumska inteligencija koju smo zaboravili izgraditi","category":"space","date":"2026-03-17T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-17T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Part 1: Kada su leo breiman i adele cutler 1995.","execSummary":"RFX-Fuse revives Breiman and Cutler’s original Random Forest vision as a *true* unified ML engine—classification, similarity, outlier detection, and more in a single model. For scientific missions (e.g., satellite data analysis), this reduces toolchain fragmentation by 60-80%, but the real test is whether its integrated approach sacrifices rigor for convenience. The bigger question: Can consolidated models change how we design exploration pipelines?","keyPoints":["Breimanov i Cutlerov izvorni Random Forest – napokon cjelovit","Jedan model umjesto pet alata u suvremenim ML pipeline-ovima","GPU podrška za ubrzanu proximitetnu sličnost i detekciju anomala"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/rfx-fuse-revives-breimans-lost-vision-for-machine-/main.jpg","alt":"RFX-Fuse: Šumska inteligencija koju smo zaboravili izgraditi"},"subtitle":"Zašto je unifikirani ML engine važan za znanstvenu eksploraciju podataka","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/rfx-fuse-revives-breimans-lost-vision-for-machine-/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Zašto je unifikirani ML engine važan za znanstvenu eksploraciju podataka"},"tags":["RFX-Fuse","Machine Learning Engine","Space Data Exploration"],"geo":{"name":"Santa Clara, CA","lat":37.3875,"lon":-122.0575,"